Title: Hopf reductions, fluxes and branes
Authors: Ruben Minasian and Dimitrios Tsimpis
Comments: 22 pages, harvmac; minor corrections, note added; Section 4
  corrected; Powers of string coupling fixed, topology of the solution in
  section 4.1 clarified, to appear in Nucl.Phys.B
Report-no: CPHT-S032.0601
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B613 (2001) 127-146
\\
  We use a series of reductions, T-dualities and liftings to construct
connections between fractional brane solutions in IIA, IIB and M-theory. We
find a number of phantom branes that are not supported by the geometry, however
materialize upon untwisting and/or Hopf-reduction.
